Youre right I wasnt trying to make a blanket statement, I was just speaking from my experience.  It really depends on the kid amd the oarent and a whole bunch of things.

Being a child (f23) of two single parents I didnt mind my main parent (dad) bringing around a bunch of girlfriends. I was always priority and it never bothered me or made me jealous or anything. 

On the other hand, my mother never introduced me to any of her partners and when she did find a husband i flipped out and had a huge meltdown and it honestly changed my life in a negative way. The guy is great and now its fine but it really affected me. I felt abandpnded and left out.

I think if youre a primary caretaker, your kids wont mind meeting casual partners so much because they just want you to be happy and can give you their opinion of the person before you fully commit.
